  "instructions": [
    "Rinse the borlotti beans and soak them in water for at least 8 hours.",
    "Drain and rinse the soaked borlotti beans, then transfer them to a blender or food processor.",
    "Add the onion, garlic, cumin, coriander, smoked paprika, salt, and black pepper to the blender and blend until well combined.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat, then add the blended mixture and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Add the soaked borlotti beans, water, and parsley to the saucepan, then bring to a boil and simmer for 20-25 minutes, or until the beans are tender.",
    "Stir in the lemon juice and cook for 1-2 minutes, then remove from heat.",
    "Let cool slightly, then stir in the chopped fresh cilantro.",
    "Serve warm or at room temperature.",
    "Garnish with additional parsley or cilantro if desired."
  ],
